Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper discusses applications in point cloud and mesh registration, pose graph optimization, and image-based object pose estimation, which are all related to computer vision.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper mentions robotics problems and their solutions using Semidefinite Programming and Sums-of-Squares relaxations.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of robust cost functions and the Black-Rangarajan duality, which are related to machine learning techniques.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a general-purpose approach for robust global estimation, which can be applied to any problem where a non-minimal solver is available for the outlier-free case, and this can be considered as an AI problem.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of non-minimal solvers and robust estimation for spatial perception, which can be considered as a systems and control problem.
